'1,3-Dibromopropane' is a halogenated hydrocarbon. When at room temperature, it
is a colorless to light-brown liquid. Synthetically, it is very useful to form
C 3-bridged compounds such as through C-N coupling reactions.

1,3-Dibromopropane was used in the first cyclopropane synthesis in 1881, the
Freund reaction.
